<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7397> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7397" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Honored as legatus pro praetore in an unpublished inscription of Cos, reported by Herzog, who suggested a date in the early first century. He might be a son of the consul of 139 (22) and father of Paulla Popillia (33), wife of the Cn. Piso (69), who is mentioned as a Catilinarian (MRR 2.159). See Münzer, Klio 24, 1931, 338.[168x]" .
